<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="/css/style.css">
    <link rel="icon" href="/img/weather.png">
    <title>About Page</title>
</head>
<body>
    <div class="main-content">
        {{>header}}
        
        <div class="about-content">
            <h1>About the Developer</h1>
            <p>
                <img src="/img/Yuval.png" class="portrait" alt="Yuval's Portrait">
            </p>  
            <p>Hello! I'm Yuval Aharon, a passionate full-stack developer with a love for creating user-friendly applications. This Weather App is a project from my Node.js studies, where I focused on learning Express, Handlebars, and working with APIs to deliver real-time weather data.</p>
            
            <h2>About This App</h2>
            <p>This weather app allows users to search for up-to-date weather information by entering a location. It fetches data through reliable weather APIs and presents it in a simple, accessible format, making it easy for users to stay informed.</p>

            <h2>Technologies Used</h2>
            <ul>
                <li>Node.js & Express for server setup and routing</li>
                <li>Handlebars for dynamic HTML templates</li>
                <li>CSS for responsive and modern styling</li>
            </ul>
        </div>
        
        {{>footer}}
    </div>
</body>
</html>
